During Older Americans Month, President Biden honors the contributions of seniors to the United States and emphasizes the importance of supporting and respecting older adults. He recognizes the strength and resilience of older Americans, particularly during the pandemic, where many seniors served in healthcare and education roles. The American Rescue Plan provides funding for services and support for older adults, including nutrition, health promotion, disease prevention, caregiver support, and long-term care. The administration is also committed to improving the safety and quality of care in nursing homes. President Biden highlights the 50th anniversary of the Older Americans Act Nutrition Program and the 10th anniversary of the National Plan to Address Alzheimer's Disease. He calls upon all Americans to celebrate older adults, support their independence, and acknowledge their value to the nation.